{
  "stem": "304.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only at the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not the others.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were exposed already as-- as-- I always felt, as far as I can go in memory, that I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I wasn't-- Are you saying that-- that the-- that Jewish children usually had more lice?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Or are you saying that they-- why would they not have checked the peasant children?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they would check the Jewish children for lice?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were Jewish children who came from a poor neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe they had some lice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know if the non-Jewish had lice, because I only remember that they looked at the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't think they had more lice than the non-Jewish children, but this is one way to-- to--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Put them down.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Put-- put us down, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then in elementary school I remember also-- we had, in Czechoslovakia-- I'm still talking about Czechoslovakia before '39-- boy Jewish children had separate classes in elementary schools.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A Jewish class and a non-Jewish class.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember in fourth grade the principal came in and picked out four girls who were straight-A students and took them to the non-Jewish class so they will lift up the level of the class.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he took out, but-- but the rest we stayed in the class.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So those are my memories from-- from the Czech democracy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what happened later, it was quite good.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What do you mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What happened later when the war broke up and the Hungarians came in, and then the Germans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So-- but-- I mean, under the Czechs, we-- my father had his business.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was in the lumber business.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we could-- we-- we were free people, even though in certain places and certain parts, we were discriminated or we didn't feel comfortable.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
